<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2186: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-22T14:00:00+09:00">August 22,
                                    1941—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 22—4:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1286. For the Secretary and the Under Secretary only. Embassy’s 1267,
                            August 18, 9 p.m. The Minister for Foreign Affairs sent me word this
                            morning through the Director of the American Bureau that the German
                            Ambassador had yesterday called on Admiral Toyoda and had asked what was
                            the subject of the conversation which I had with Admiral Toyoda on
                            August 18, and that Admiral Toyoda had informed the German Ambassador
                            that I had called to make representations with regard to a number of
                            specific cases of difficulties experienced by Americans in Japan and
                            China.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>